# Mongoose Model Rules

## Schema Conventions
- Export the Mongoose model from each file (e.g., `export const UserModel = mongoose.model<...>()`).
- Keep `userId` as a `ref: 'User'` on `Product` and `Order` documents.
- Define static helpers on the schema with `modelSchema.statics.*` and mirror them in a static interface type.

## Model Inventory
| File | Export | Key Feature |
|---|---|---|
| `user.model.ts` | `UserModel` | Cart instance methods + static helpers |
| `product.model.ts` | `Product` | `userId` ref to `User` |
| `order.model.ts` | `OrderModel` | `products[]` with embedded product ref + quantity |
| `token.model.ts` | `TokenModel` | `userId` ref to `User`, `token` string |
| `node-mail.model.ts` | `NodeMailModel` | Email sending + JWT reset-password helpers |

## UserModel Static Methods
- `isValidEmail(email): boolean` — regex test for basic email format.
- `isPasswordLengthIsOk(password): boolean` — returns `true` when `password.length <= 72`.
- `getUserByEmail(email): Promise<User | null>` — wraps `findOne({email})`.
- `isUserExistByEmail(email): Promise<boolean>` — returns `true` when user exists.

## UserModel Instance Methods (on `userSchema.methods`)
- `addToCart(product)` — adds product or increments quantity; marks `cart` modified before save.
- `deleteProductFromCart(productId)` — filters out item matching `productId`, then saves.
- `clearCart()` — resets `cart.items` to `[]` and saves.
- When adding a new instance method, extend the Mongoose document type accordingly.

## NodeMailModel Statics
- `sendWelcomeEmail(email, name)` — sends welcome email; errors are caught and logged.
- `sendResetPasswordEmail(email, link)` — sends reset password email; errors are caught and logged.
- `createResetPasswordToken(email)` — signs JWT `{ email }` with `env.sessionSecret`, expires `1h`.
- `verifyResetPasswordToken(token)` — verifies JWT, returns `{ email, iat, exp }` or `null`.
- `getResetPasswordTokenLink(email, token?)` — builds the full reset-password URL using `env.url`.

## Population Pattern
- Cart products: nested populate `cart.items.productId` (see `shop.controller.ts#getCart`).
- Orders: `products[].product` is a ref to `Product`; `products[].quantity` is a Number.

## Do Not
- Do not use raw SQL-style syntax — use Mongoose query API.
- Do not call `.save()` on a document fetched via `.lean()` — it returns a plain object.
- Do not define cart/order mutation logic in controllers — keep it in `userSchema.methods`.

